[
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there a <a href=\"https://specifications.freedesktop.org/shared-mime-info-spec/latest/ar01s02.html#id-1.3.5\">MIME type file</a> for Lean 4 source code files? I'm trying to set a default application for opening .lean files and it seems like I need this to apply a default to just those instead of all text files.</p>",
        "id": 525212224,
        "sender_full_name": "Raghuram",
        "timestamp": 1750597485
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In case it isn't, here's a very basic one people may find useful:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"XML\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"nt\">&lt;mime-info</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"na\">xmlns=</span><span class=\"s\">\"http://www.freedesktop.org/standards/shared-mime-info\"</span><span class=\"nt\">&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nt\">&lt;mime-type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"na\">type=</span><span class=\"s\">\"text/x-lean4\"</span><span class=\"nt\">&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nt\">&lt;comment&gt;</span>Lean<span class=\"w\"> </span>4<span class=\"w\"> </span>source<span class=\"w\"> </span>code<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/comment&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nt\">&lt;sub-class-of</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"na\">type=</span><span class=\"s\">\"text/plain\"</span><span class=\"nt\">/&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nt\">&lt;glob</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"na\">pattern=</span><span class=\"s\">\"*.lean\"</span><span class=\"nt\">/&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nt\">&lt;/mime-type&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"nt\">&lt;/mime-info&gt;</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 525213111,
        "sender_full_name": "Raghuram",
        "timestamp": 1750598662
    }
]